### ========================================
### 12. ERROR HANDLING TESTS
### ========================================

### Invalid Login Credentials
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "nonexistent",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Register Duplicate Username
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser001",
  "email": "another@example.com",
  "password": "AnotherPassword123"
}

###

### Duplicate Email
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "anotheruser",
  "email": "testuser001@example.com",
  "password": "AnotherPassword123"
}

###

### Empty Username
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

###

### Invalid Email Format
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "Password123"
}

###

### Short Password
POST http://localhost:8082/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "short"
}

###

### Access Protected Resource without Token
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/quantities
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Access Protected Resource with Invalid Token
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/quantities
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_format

###

